article.headline: Florida A&M 83, Winston-Salem 68
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) -- Rome Sanders scored 24 points to help Florida A&M cruise to a 83-68 win over Winston-Salem Monday. The Rattlers dominated the inside, outrebounding the Rams 50-30 and outscoring them 36-16 in the paint. Florida A&M (13-9, 8-2 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) used a 16-3 run midway through the first half to take control of the game, and led 43-26 at the break. The Rattlers' 13 second half turnovers allowed Winston-Salem to close within nine points, but Florida A&M answered with an 11-3 run to seal the game. Sanders was 9-of-15 from the field, and added six rebounds. Darius Glover came off the bench to score 15 points and pull down 10 rebounds, and Akini Adkins added 12 points and nine rebounds. Florida A&M dished out 17 assists and led the entire way. Darius Floyd scored a game high 27 points for Winston-Salem (4-20, 0-9) and Brian Fisher added 15.
